Creating images with R

Cheryl Qiu

2023-03-13

My meme

My meme is based on the honey badger, a tough fearless animal from Africa. Cats have the attitudes of honey badgers but they lack the skills and abilities to back this up. So I think its funny to put them together. There are three characters in my meme, a honey badger, a typical cat and another cat who tells the fact.

library(magick)

# square one
honey_badger <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/ff/75/6f/ff756f1f34f7eb0bf20de475413cc8e5.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# square two
hb_text <- image_blank(width = 600,
                       height = 500,
                       color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Lions? Eagles? Snakes?\nI don't care!",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# square three
grumpy_cat <- image_read("https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQ4MjU2NDE1OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTk2ODMxMDE@._V1_.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# square four
gc_text <- image_blank(width = 600,
                       height = 500,
                       color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "If honey badger doesn't care,\nyou think I should?",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# square five
wise_cat <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/7a/4f/ab/7a4fab6aed9c1f2dc8e36c126e21f198.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)


# square six
wc_text <- image_blank(width = 600,
                       height = 500,
                       color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Hmmmm.\nYes, you should.",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# making each row
first_row <- c(honey_badger, hb_text) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(grumpy_cat, gc_text) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(wise_cat, wc_text) %>%
  image_append()

# combine the three rows together
meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE)

image_write(meme,"my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

Slam Dunk was an important anime in 1990s. I used to watch this on TV when I was a kid. Recently Slam Dunk was rebooted with a new movie. Creating a GIF about this is topical. I selected the images of the five main characters in the anime and showing their names on the images.

library(magick)

# creating names vector
names <- c("Akagi\nTakenori", "Miyagi\nRyouta", "Rukawa\nKaede", "Mitsui\nHisashi", "Sakuragi\nHanamichi")

# linking names to the images
akagi <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/0a/17/67/0a176717611c5a51d30eb1d465cb8035.jpg")

miyagi <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/60/68/c3/6068c3f263d6cfea3fbeecd97cb934bf.jpg")

rukawa <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/1a/8c/0d/1a8c0d1f52bb290af0b89f78f578ec21.jpg")

mitsui <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/9f/94/e7/9f94e718a985fe743b04ef73ec8e2b65.jpg")

sakuragi <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/ca/ec/a4/caeca4b9fe3e429dd1d3ef9e40d07058.jpg")

# creating each frame, where the text comes from the names vector
frame1 <- akagi %>%
  image_annotate(text = names[1], color = "#0000ff", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "north-west") %>%
  image_scale(300)

frame2 <- miyagi %>%
  image_annotate(text = names[2], color = "#000000", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "north-west") %>%
  image_scale(300) 

frame3 <- rukawa %>%
  image_annotate(text = names[3], color = "#000000", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "south-west") %>%
  image_scale(300)

frame4 <- mitsui %>%
  image_annotate(text = names[4], color = "#0000ff", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "south-west") %>%
  image_scale(300)

frame5 <- sakuragi %>%
  image_annotate(text = names[5], color = "#ffffff", font = "Impact", size = 80, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5)

# creating an animation
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
